summary: For the pokemon ask: electric type!
question: For the pokemon ask: electric type!
answer:
favorite: this ask made me realize I don’t exactly have electric types at the top of my list! So I’ll pick a pokemon that did well for me in Diamond battles - Luxray. very good pokemon. what a good lion!

second favorite: again, I don’t feel super strongly about any electric types, but I always though Jolteon’s design was cool! He’s my second favorite eeveelution (the 1st favorite being Leafeon/Glaceon, tied.)

cutest: Okay there are some great designs for electric types. I REALLY cant choose who’s cuter - Blitzle, or Joltik. WTF!! I can’t believe there are TEENY TWO-FOOT ZEBRAS RUNNIN AROUND. that’s adorable. <3

least favorite: I actually don’t dislike any of the electric types…. except Pikachu. He’s a basic bitch and he gets SO much media attention and he’s not even the best Pokemon. All merchandise focuses on the yellow rat, and almost NO light is given to any of the cooler ones. I get it, he’s the official mascot, but I’m just. so tired of pikachu. @hanbei-l-of-ransei is also a fellow pikachu hater I believe hahahhaa

blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Cryogonal
body:
615: Cryogonal

When this thing was first released, I was really split on it. Even as someone that liked a lot of inanimate object Pokemon, Cryogonal was just. Weird. A floating snowflake with a face? Interesting, but weird. But over the years, long after the thing’s been long-forgotten by fans, I’ve begun growing a bit of an appreciation for the weirdo. It’s so visually different from any other Pokemon, even other objectmon. With a jagged face and features, eerie glowing eyes and mouth-dangly-bits. Mouth-dangly-bits that apparently entangle prey for it to consume. Yes. The floating snowflake is carnivorous. What a world the Pokemon world is.

It apparently acts just like snow does as well. When it melts, it immediately evaporates into gas and floats up into the atmosphere to freeze and reform itself. Which it’ll then descend to the surface once more to snare another victim. It’s such a freaky idea for a monster, not to mention eerie. It’s absolutely hilarious that an oversized snowflake is one of the most visually unnerving Pokemon out there. The fact Cryogonal exists at all is weird and I love it.

Personal Score: 9/10

Not a Pokemon I expected to give a 9/10. Nice!

[Archive]
